48#define INT_GPIOA 16 // GPIO Port A
49#define INT_GPIOB 17 // GPIO Port B

52#define INT_GPIOE 20 // GPIO Port E

70#define INT_TIMER1B 38 // 16/32-Bit Timer 1B
71#define INT_TIMER2A 39 // 16/32-Bit Timer 2A
72#define INT_TIMER2B 40 // 16/32-Bit Timer 2B
73#define INT_COMP0 41 // Analog Comparator 0
74#define INT_COMP1 42 // Analog Comparator 1
75#define INT_COMP2 43 // Analog Comparator 2
76#define INT_SYSCTL 44 // System Control
77#define INT_FLASH 45 // Flash Memory Control

79#define INT_GPIOG 47 // GPIO Port G
80#define INT_GPIOH 48 // GPIO Port H
81#define INT_UART2 49 // UART2

91#define INT_UDMA 60 // uDMA 0 Software
92#define INT_UDMAERR 61 // uDMA 0 Error
93#define INT_ADC1SS0 62 // ADC1 Sequence 0
94#define INT_ADC1SS1 63 // ADC1 Sequence 1
95#define INT_ADC1SS2 64 // ADC1 Sequence 2
96#define INT_ADC1SS3 65 // ADC1 Sequence 3
97#define INT_EPI0 66 // EPI 0
98#define INT_GPIOJ 67 // GPIO Port J
99#define INT_GPIOK 68 // GPIO Port K
100#define INT_GPIOL 69 // GPIO Port L
101#define INT_SSI2 70 // SSI 2

105#define INT_UART5 74 // UART 5
106#define INT_UART6 75 // UART 6

110#define INT_TIMER4A 79 // Timer 4A
111#define INT_TIMER4B 80 // Timer 4B
112#define INT_TIMER5A 81 // Timer 5A
113#define INT_TIMER5B 82 // Timer 5B
114#define INT_SYSEXC 83 // Floating-Point Exception
115 // (imprecise)

149//*****************************************************************************
150//
151// Watchdog Timer registers (WATCHDOG0)
152//
153//*****************************************************************************
154#define WATCHDOG0_LOAD_R (*((volatile uint32_t *)0x40000000))
155#define WATCHDOG0_VALUE_R (*((volatile uint32_t *)0x40000004))
156#define WATCHDOG0_CTL_R (*((volatile uint32_t *)0x40000008))
157#define WATCHDOG0_ICR_R (*((volatile uint32_t *)0x4000000C))
158#define WATCHDOG0_RIS_R (*((volatile uint32_t *)0x40000010))
159#define WATCHDOG0_MIS_R (*((volatile uint32_t *)0x40000014))
160#define WATCHDOG0_TEST_R (*((volatile uint32_t *)0x40000418))
161#define WATCHDOG0_LOCK_R (*((volatile uint32_t *)0x40000C00))
162

6918#define ADC_PC_MCR_1_8 0x00000001 // Eighth conversion rate. After a
6919 // conversion completes, the logic
6920 // pauses for 112 TADC periods
6921 // before starting the next
6922 // conversion
6923#define ADC_PC_MCR_1_4 0x00000003 // Quarter conversion rate. After a
6924 // conversion completes, the logic
6925 // pauses for 48 TADC periods
6926 // before starting the next
6927 // conversion
6928#define ADC_PC_MCR_1_2 0x00000005 // Half conversion rate. After a
6929 // conversion completes, the logic
6930 // pauses for 16 TADC periods
6931 // before starting the next
6932 // conversion
6933#define ADC_PC_MCR_FULL 0x00000007 // Full conversion rate (FCONV) as
6934 // defined by TADC and NSH

9859 // transaction with a STALL

10135 0x00000000 // This setting is the default. If
10136 // there is no password, the block
10137 // is not protected and is readable
10138 // and writable
10139#define EEPROM_EEPROT_PROT_RWPW 0x00000001 // If there is a password, the
10140 // block is readable or writable
10141 // only when unlocked
10142#define EEPROM_EEPROT_PROT_RONPW \
10143 0x00000002 // If there is no password, the
10144 // block is readable, not writable
10145

10639//*****************************************************************************
10640//
10641// The following are defines for the bit fields in the EPI_O_FIFOLVL register.
10642//
10643//*****************************************************************************
10644#define EPI_FIFOLVL_WFERR 0x00020000 // Write Full Error
10645#define EPI_FIFOLVL_RSERR 0x00010000 // Read Stall Error
10646#define EPI_FIFOLVL_WRFIFO_M 0x00000070 // Write FIFO
10647#define EPI_FIFOLVL_WRFIFO_EMPT 0x00000000 // Interrupt is triggered while
10648 // WRFIFO is empty.
10649#define EPI_FIFOLVL_WRFIFO_2 0x00000020 // Interrupt is triggered until
10650 // there are only two slots
10651 // available. Thus, trigger is
10652 // deasserted when there are two
10653 // WRFIFO entries present. This
10654 // configuration is optimized for
10655 // bursts of 2
10656#define EPI_FIFOLVL_WRFIFO_1 0x00000030 // Interrupt is triggered until
10657 // there is one WRFIFO entry
10658 // available. This configuration
10659 // expects only single writes
10660#define EPI_FIFOLVL_WRFIFO_NFULL \
10661 0x00000040 // Trigger interrupt when WRFIFO is
10662 // not full, meaning trigger will
10663 // continue to assert until there
10664 // are four entries in the WRFIFO
10665#define EPI_FIFOLVL_RDFIFO_M 0x00000007 // Read FIFO
10666#define EPI_FIFOLVL_RDFIFO_1 0x00000001 // Trigger when there are 1 or more
10667 // entries in the NBRFIFO
10668#define EPI_FIFOLVL_RDFIFO_2 0x00000002 // Trigger when there are 2 or more
10669 // entries in the NBRFIFO
10670#define EPI_FIFOLVL_RDFIFO_4 0x00000003 // Trigger when there are 4 or more
10671 // entries in the NBRFIFO
10672#define EPI_FIFOLVL_RDFIFO_6 0x00000004 // Trigger when there are 6 or more
10673 // entries in the NBRFIFO
10674#define EPI_FIFOLVL_RDFIFO_7 0x00000005 // Trigger when there are 7 or more
10675 // entries in the NBRFIFO
10676#define EPI_FIFOLVL_RDFIFO_8 0x00000006 // Trigger when there are 8 entries
10677 // in the NBRFIFO
10678

14320#define CCM_CRCCTRL_ENDIAN_SBHW 0x00000000 // Configuration unchanged. (B3,
14321 // B2, B1, B0)
14322#define CCM_CRCCTRL_ENDIAN_SHW 0x00000010 // Bytes are swapped in half-words
14323 // but half-words are not swapped
14324 // (B2, B3, B0, B1)
14325#define CCM_CRCCTRL_ENDIAN_SHWNB \
14326 0x00000020 // Half-words are swapped but bytes
14327 // are not swapped in half-word.
14328 // (B1, B0, B3, B2)
14329#define CCM_CRCCTRL_ENDIAN_SBSW 0x00000030 // Bytes are swapped in half-words
14330 // and half-words are swapped. (B0,
14331 // B1, B2, B3)

14333#define CCM_CRCCTRL_TYPE_P8055 0x00000000 // Polynomial 0x8005

14982//*****************************************************************************
14983//
14984// The following are defines for the bit fields in the AES_O_CTRL register.
14985//
14986//*****************************************************************************
14987#define AES_CTRL_CTXTRDY 0x80000000 // Context Data Registers Ready
14988#define AES_CTRL_SVCTXTRDY 0x40000000 // AES TAG/IV Block(s) Ready
14989#define AES_CTRL_SAVE_CONTEXT 0x20000000 // TAG or Result IV Save
14990#define AES_CTRL_CCM_M_M 0x01C00000 // Counter with CBC-MAC (CCM)
14991#define AES_CTRL_CCM_L_M 0x00380000 // L Value
14992#define AES_CTRL_CCM_L_2 0x00080000 // width = 2
14993#define AES_CTRL_CCM_L_4 0x00180000 // width = 4
14994#define AES_CTRL_CCM_L_8 0x00380000 // width = 8
14995#define AES_CTRL_CCM 0x00040000 // AES-CCM Mode Enable
14996#define AES_CTRL_GCM_M 0x00030000 // AES-GCM Mode Enable
14997#define AES_CTRL_GCM_NOP 0x00000000 // No operation
14998#define AES_CTRL_GCM_HLY0ZERO 0x00010000 // GHASH with H loaded and
14999 // Y0-encrypted forced to zero
15000#define AES_CTRL_GCM_HLY0CALC 0x00020000 // GHASH with H loaded and
15001 // Y0-encrypted calculated
15002 // internally
15003#define AES_CTRL_GCM_HY0CALC 0x00030000 // Autonomous GHASH (both H and
15004 // Y0-encrypted calculated
15005 // internally)
15006#define AES_CTRL_CBCMAC 0x00008000 // AES-CBC MAC Enable
15007#define AES_CTRL_F9 0x00004000 // AES f9 Mode Enable
15008#define AES_CTRL_F8 0x00002000 // AES f8 Mode Enable
15009#define AES_CTRL_XTS_M 0x00001800 // AES-XTS Operation Enabled
15010#define AES_CTRL_XTS_NOP 0x00000000 // No operation
15011#define AES_CTRL_XTS_TWEAKJL 0x00000800 // Previous/intermediate tweak
15012 // value and j loaded (value is
15013 // loaded via IV, j is loaded via
15014 // the AAD length register)
15015#define AES_CTRL_XTS_K2IJL 0x00001000 // Key2, n and j are loaded (n is
15016 // loaded via IV, j is loaded via
15017 // the AAD length register)
15018#define AES_CTRL_XTS_K2ILJ0 0x00001800 // Key2 and n are loaded; j=0 (n is
15019 // loaded via IV)
15020#define AES_CTRL_CFB 0x00000400 // Full block AES cipher feedback
15021 // mode (CFB128) Enable
15022#define AES_CTRL_ICM 0x00000200 // AES Integer Counter Mode (ICM)
15023 // Enable
15024#define AES_CTRL_CTR_WIDTH_M 0x00000180 // AES-CTR Mode Counter Width
15025#define AES_CTRL_CTR_WIDTH_32 0x00000000 // Counter is 32 bits
15026#define AES_CTRL_CTR_WIDTH_64 0x00000080 // Counter is 64 bits
15027#define AES_CTRL_CTR_WIDTH_96 0x00000100 // Counter is 96 bits
15028#define AES_CTRL_CTR_WIDTH_128 0x00000180 // Counter is 128 bits
15029#define AES_CTRL_CTR 0x00000040 // Counter Mode
15030#define AES_CTRL_MODE 0x00000020 // ECB/CBC Mode
15031#define AES_CTRL_KEY_SIZE_M 0x00000018 // Key Size
15032#define AES_CTRL_KEY_SIZE_128 0x00000008 // Key is 128 bits
15033#define AES_CTRL_KEY_SIZE_192 0x00000010 // Key is 192 bits
15034#define AES_CTRL_KEY_SIZE_256 0x00000018 // Key is 256 bits
15035#define AES_CTRL_DIRECTION 0x00000004 // Encryption/Decryption Selection
15036#define AES_CTRL_INPUT_READY 0x00000002 // Input Ready Status
15037#define AES_CTRL_OUTPUT_READY 0x00000001 // Output Ready Status
15038#define AES_CTRL_CCM_M_S 22
15039

15351 // Encryption is selected
